Leaf Clean Energy Co. (LEAF) , a Cayman
Islands-based investor in renewable energy projects, said one of
its portfolio companies raised $32.5 million in equity through
selling preferred stock to funds managed by Invesco Asset
Management Ltd.  Leaf also sold 1.8 million common shares in the company,
MaxWest, for $900,000, Leaf said today in a filing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Todd White at 
 twhite2@bloomberg.net  